\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish mandatory controls for maintaining the integrity of Elko County information systems.
 This policy mandates the implementation of malicious code protection,
 system monitoring,
 and integrity verification mechanisms to detect and prevent unauthorized changes,
 exploitation,
 and data corruption.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations (ECIO) personnel,
 employees,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and volunteers,
 and all information systems,
 networks,
 and endpoints owned,
 leased,
 or operated by Elko County.
 This specifically includes all systems that process,
 store,
 or transmit Criminal Justice Information (CJI) and the infrastructure supporting these systems.
\end_layout

